caption: b'Meet Mansi Sanghvi, an engineer at our Bayway Refinery, who dedicates herself to providing energy and improving lives \xe2\x80\x94 on the job and in her community. She leads fundraising efforts while at work and represents Phillips 66 on the board of local organizations. Read more about Mansi\xe2\x80\x99s incredible work through the link in our bio.'

b'Affordable, reliable energy has a lot of moving parts. But it\xe2\x80\x99s also got a lot of storage, terminaling, fractionators and facilities in its infrastructure. Good thing our Midstream segment can handle it all.'
b'Another day in Big Sky Country. We keep energy moving in the Northwestern United States with transportation fuels and fuel-grade petroleum coke produced at our Billings Refinery. #ArtofEnergy'

b'With a new state-of-the-art training facility \xe2\x80\x93 complete with virtual reality room \xe2\x80\x93 safety training is getting a modern boost at Phillips 66 Humber Refinery in the U.K. Learn more by visiting the link in our bio.'

b'Being a good neighbor means giving thanks and giving back. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we support education programs, sustainability efforts and more, in the places where we live and work. By partnering with local organizations, we strengthen our communities and power a brighter tomorrow.'

b'Supporting the business, maintaining operational excellence and environmental stewardship are on our minds 24/7 at the Phillips 66 Research Center in Bartlesville, OK. Here, we conduct research to enhance the safety and reliability of our operations and evaluate technologies that will power the next generation of energy solutions \xe2\x80\x94 like flexible solar films made from high-performance specialty organic materials and more.'

b'Wondering who can use renewable fuels? Chances are you can. Watch the video here to learn more about how drop-in renewable fuels can be used in everyday transportation and read more about our efforts to fuel a lower carbon future at RodeoRenewed.com. Link in bio.'

b'Phillips 66 Humber Refinery is the first refinery in the U.K. to convert cooking oil into fuel \xe2\x80\x94 and it just got a boost from a 50-foot tall, 80-ton new module to process used cooking oil. The new module, delivered atop a self-propelled transporter, is set to triple Humber\xe2\x80\x99s renewable diesel capacity by January 2021 to 3,000 barrels per day. Congratulations to the hard-working teams who are helping us work toward a lower-carbon future in the U.K. and beyond. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'We are quadrupling capacity to process natural gas liquids at our Sweeny Hub in Texas with the startup of two new, state-of-the-art fractionators. Learn more about this world-class project by visiting the link in our bio.'

b'Public access to natural ecosystems goes hand-in-hand with conservation efforts, which is why we\xe2\x80\x99re strong supporters of the Texas Parks and Wildlife Foundation. Through donations, we\xe2\x80\x99re helping to protect critical wildlife habitats and provide access for visitors to learn about Texas\xe2\x80\x99 many unique ecosystems all year.'

b'At Phillips 66 we have a nationwide network of terminals that help us ensure crude and refined products can be delivered and stored in safe and effective ways. Take a look at the Wink Facility in West Texas, one of our safe, secure storage sites along the Gray Oak Pipeline. #ArtofEnergy'

b'Today is National STEM Day! And here at Phillips 66, we proudly support STEM-powered organizations every day. Encouraging young learners to explore their world through the principles of STEM promotes critical thinking, boosts confidence and helps prepare today\xe2\x80\x99s students to be the innovative leaders of tomorrow. :woman_scientist_medium_skin_tone::woman_technologist: :man_astronaut_medium_skin_tone: :man_teacher: #NationalSTEMDay'

b'Native landscaping of any size provide beauty and ecological benefits in our communities, which is why, with the help of the Wildlife Habitat Council, Phillips 66 developed resources to help our station owners create their own landscaping. Our region-specific guides on native landscaping can be found through the link in our bio.'

b'Our employees value volunteering their time to organizations in our communities. Like @HabitatHouston, an organization who has increased safety precautions so volunteers can continue to dedicate their time and passion to building a strong foundation for our communities.'
b'At Phillips 66, we provide the products and energy that help people go farther, dream bigger and climb higher. Thanks to our employees, we keep energy moving forward. #ArtofEnergy'

b'Happy Halloween! The Phillips 66 Los Angeles Refinery\xe2\x80\x99s iconic 3.3-million gallon jack-o\xe2\x80\x99-lantern is back for Halloween! Smilin\xe2\x80\x99 Jack has been a tradition at the refinery and in the L.A. community since 1952. This year, Smilin\xe2\x80\x99 Jack sports a new look, wearing a face mask as a symbol of our commitment to safety, no matter the season. :jack-o-lantern:'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re making a bold commitment to renewable fuels. Once operational, Rodeo Renewed could produce more than 800 million gallons of renewable gas, diesel, and jet fuel\xe2\x80\x94all of which help improve air quality. Visit the link in our bio to read more about the benefits and learn how you can get involved.'

b'For over a decade, Phillips 66 has worked with the USA Swimming Foundation to raise awareness about the importance of safety in and around the water. Keeping pools open year round, so kids can learn to swim, helps save lives. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'Our fuel brands are connected by a network of 13 refineries, 200 terminals, 7,540 branded U.S. stations and 1,600 branded international stations. At Phillips 66, we keep things moving with a supply chain that helps transport fuel at home and abroad.'
b'Thank you for taking us along for another great season, Houston Astros. Continue swinging for the fences, and the Phillips 66 Home Run Pump will keep count.'

b'The Boys and Girls Club of Greater Houston recently honored Phillips 66 for our longstanding support and shared mission of helping the city\xe2\x80\x99s youth at their virtual 2020 Great Futures Dinner. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'Energy is always on the go at our Beaumont Terminal in Nederland, Texas. It\xe2\x80\x99s our largest terminal and has storage capacity for 16.8 million barrels of crude oil and refined petroleum products. #ArtofEnergy'

b'We know there\xe2\x80\x99s no one-size-fits all solution when it comes to sending kids back to school. That\xe2\x80\x99s why Phillips 66 is working closely with school districts in our communities to help find specific, impactful and lasting solutions that will help ensure our students can learn safely and effectively. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'At Phillips 66, our commitment to the safety of everyone who works in our operating facilities and offices is unwavering. As a leader in our industry, we took and continue to take innovative and proactive safety measures to protect our workers and the public during the COVID-19 pandemic. We\xe2\x80\x99ve invested over $4.6 million in personal protective equipment (PPE) to keep our employees safe and healthy and remain diligent with our strategy of social distancing, temperature checks, practicing good hygiene and keeping common surfaces clean, so we can continue to bring energy to our communities.'

b'Happy National Techies Day! Thanks to our many engineers, scientists and researchers who work at the forefront of the latest tech, we\xe2\x80\x99ve been ahead of the game since way back in the day. #NationalTechiesDay'

b'Closing out a great season with the 2,000th recorded home run hit at Minute Maid Park and the Phillips 66 Home Run Pump has been there to capture them from the start. Good luck in the playoffs, @astrosbaseball! #ForTheH'

b'You\xe2\x80\x99ve heard us talk about \xe2\x80\x9crenewable fuels,\xe2\x80\x9d but what are they? Watch this video to find out and visit the link in our bio to learn more about our plans to support demand for renewable fuels and help California meet its low-carbon objectives.'

b'Our lubricants brands include Phillips 66, Kendall Motor Oil, Red Line Oil and other private label brands. With world-class research & development and manufacturing facilities, we supply over 80 countries worldwide with automotive, commercial, industrial and specialty lubricants.'
b'Rounding out the day with a look at one of the spheroid storage tanks at our Los Angeles Refinery. #ArtofEnergy'
b'Back in time and behind the scenes. Here at Phillips 66, we have a long history of working to meet the energy demands of today while always focusing on the needs of tomorrow.'

b'Phillips 66 Aviation has been the wind beneath some pretty impressive wings. We\xe2\x80\x99ve been a top supplier of jet fuel and avgas to private, commercial and military aviation for over 90 years. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'At Phillips 66, we know how important it is to support organizations like the American Red Cross. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we committed $1 million to the organization in support of disaster relief this past month, including $200,000 to help supply shelter, food and emergency relief to communities in Northern California after wildfires displaced thousands of people.'

b'Phillips 66 will contribute $750,000 to the American Red Cross to support disaster relief efforts in areas impacted by Hurricane Laura. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to support the American Red Cross and its work to uplift families and communities through the recovery process. Let\xe2\x80\x99s rebuild our communities together. Visit the link in our bio to learn more.'

b'Our thoughts are with our friends and neighbors affected by Hurricane Laura. Phillips 66 continues to work with state and local officials, focusing on the safety of our employees and communities as we assess the impact from this storm. Please stay safe and visit the link in our bio for the latest updates.'
b'Our facilities are focused on maintaining the highest standards in operating excellence. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we constantly monitor our pipelines, down to the smallest detail. #ArtOfEnergy'

b'Phillips 66 is proud to announce: Rodeo Renewed. This bold new project will convert our San Francisco Refinery into the world\xe2\x80\x99s largest renewable fuels plant. Visit the link in our bio to read more.'

b'National #811Day serves as a reminder to residents and professionals alike to always #Call811 before you start your next digging project. At Phillips 66, we\xe2\x80\x99re committed to ensuring everyone who lives or works near our lines and facilities adopts safe digging practices. To learn more, visit call811.com.'

b'A record five Phillips 66 refineries earned the American Fuel and Petrochemical Manufacturers\xe2\x80\x99 highest honor, the Distinguished Safety Award. Visit the link in our bio to learn more about their outstanding performance and commitment to operating excellence.'

b'We carefully track every raw material used in our manufacturing process at 100% of our lubricants plants. In 2019, we recycled nearly 1,100 tons of scrap material from those facilities. Read more about our commitment to environmental stewardship in our 2020 sustainability report. Link in bio.'

b"We\xe2\x80\x99re pumped to cheer on the Houston Astros in their home opener tonight! The Phillips 66 Home Run Pump will keep count of every homer in Minute Maid Park this season. Let's bring home a win. #ForTheH"

b'When we design our pipelines and storage facilities, we do it with safety in mind. That means everything at our facilities is built to ensure we transport energy safely and efficiently. #ArtofEnergy'

b'While the looks of our stations may have changed over the years, our commitment to fueling our communities with affordable energy has not. Take a look back and see how our family of businesses has grown.'

b'These twists and turns tell quite the story. They\xe2\x80\x99re part of our Sweeny Hub where our teams work to produce transportation fuels and the materials that help make products for modern life. #ArtofEnergy'

b'This Fourth of July, take a moment to think about the chemistry behind a fireworks show. From the colors you see to the sounds you hear, there\xe2\x80\x99s science in every detail. Have a safe and happy holiday weekend!'

b'When you stop to refuel, follow these steps for a safer time at the pump. Avoid direct contact with surfaces by using gloves or disinfectant wipes, pay with low-touch options when available, and thoroughly clean your hands. Stay safe and healthy.'

b'At our facilities and homes, we\xe2\x80\x99re continuing to do our part to help slow the spread of COVID-19 \xe2\x80\x93 protecting one another and ourselves. We\xe2\x80\x99re in this together, even when we\xe2\x80\x99re apart. Stay vigilant and learn more on the official CDC website.'

Trinitas Regional Medical Center and the Robert Wood Johnson University Hospital will each receive $50,000 for the purchase of personal protective equipment, respirators and other essential needs. We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to support the front-line workers across our communities. #HealthCareHeroes"

b'Doing our part to keep our communities strong: Phillips 66 is contributing $3 million to COVID-19 relief efforts across its communities in the U.S. and in the U.K. The funds will be distributed to critical organizations supporting first responders, essential workers and vulnerable populations.'

b'Thank you to all of those on the front lines of the COVID-19 pandemic for keeping our communities safe. At multiple Phillips 66 locations, we are donating personal protective equipment including gloves, waterproof ponchos and goggles to local health care facilities and first responders. Together, we can help slow the spread.'

b"We're proud to light up our headquarters for April in a show of unity with those who are working to slow the spread. Whether you\xe2\x80\x99re on the front lines as a doctor or nurse, keeping the critical-infrastructure sites like ours running, or working from home, know this: We\xe2\x80\x99re all in this together. Stay safe, stay well."

b'Who said STEM is only for school? Today\xe2\x80\x99s stay-at-home learners can build their own robots with household items! All you have to do is #ThinkLikeAnEngineer :robot_face: Adult supervision required. Directions below :backhand_index_pointing_down: 
\xf0\x9d\x97\xa0\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x97\xbf\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x97\xb9\xf0\x9d\x98\x80
2 AA batteries
AA battery holder
3 volt DC motor
Corks
Scrub brush
Electrical tape
Safety goggles 
\xf0\x9d\x97\xa6\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x97\xbd\xf0\x9d\x98\x80
1. Start with the battery holder in the OFF position.
2. Insert 2 AA batteries into the holder and secure the back plating.
3. Push the motor\xe2\x80\x99s crankshaft into a cork.
NOTE: You can experiment with different sizes of cork to see which size makes your robot go. Different sizes will make the brush bot move differently.
4. Carefully tape the free edges of the black wires from the battery pack and the motor together. Then tape the free edges of the red wires together.
5. Firmly attach the battery pack and motor to a scrub brush with tape. Add some fun decorations to make your bot your own.
6. Place your brush bot onto a smooth, flat area. Switch the battery pack to the ON position and watch your brush bot go!'

b'Dolores D. Wharton and Jake Simmons Jr. were pioneers in energy and at Phillips Petroleum. Dolores was the first African American on the Phillips Petroleum board, and Jake was the first African American to broker American oil interests abroad. #BlackHistoryMonth'

b'Let\xe2\x80\x99s #ThinkLikeAnEngineer with simple circuits and the flow of electrons:light_bulb:Adult supervision required. Directions below :backhand_index_pointing_down:

\xf0\x9d\x97\xa0\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x97\xbf\xf0\x9d\x97\xb6\xf0\x9d\x97\xae\xf0\x9d\x97\xb9\xf0\x9d\x98\x80
.07 graphite
Electrical tape
6 D batteries
Small stand (a glass or a paper tube, must fit in mason jar)
Mason jar
2 wires with alligator clips
Safety goggles

\xf0\x9d\x97\xa6\xf0\x9d\x98\x81\xf0\x9d\x97\xb2\xf0\x9d\x97\xbd\xf0\x9d\x98\x80
1. Tape batteries end to end (+ to \xe2\x80\x93). 2. Adhere two alligator clips to the stand, one on each side. Leave the other ends of the wires free.

3. Secure a piece of graphite into the clips at the top of the stand.

4. Cover the entire stand with the mason jar.

5. Firmly press the free ends of the alligator clips into your battery unit \xe2\x80\x94 one clip on the positive end and one on the negative end.

NOTE: You may see smoke as the graphite heats up \xe2\x80\x94 electrons are moving quickly, producing heat and light! The graphite may be hot, even after the experiment is over, so don\xe2\x80\x99t touch it with your bare hands.

6. Wait for the electricity to circulate and watch it glow!:light_bulb:'
